        "content": "<p>I have a struct containing generic data from the driver</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[pin_data]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Job</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">credits</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">//    dependencies: List, // TODO implement dependency list</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">#[pin]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>That needs to be enqueued in my job manager, maybe so:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[pin_data]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">EnqueuedJob</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">#[pin]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">links</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ListLinks</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">KBox</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Job</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>As I see it, I have to use <code>ListLinksSelfPtr</code> as in the second example <a href=\"https://rust.docs.kernel.org/kernel/list/struct.List.html\">here</a>, right?</p>\n<p>I, however, only want to give <code>data: T</code> later back to the driver. I have no use for it in my module, I just need to transport it and take ownership over it.</p>\n<p>Do I still have to implement or demand or define a trait? It seems needed in <code>impl_list_item</code>? And wherever  <code>T</code> appears I need to ensure that it's Sized?</p>",
